se.cbb.jprime.seqevo

Class GammaSiteRateHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • se.cbb.jprime.seqevo.GammaSiteRateHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Dependent, InfoProvider, ProperDependent

    public class GammaSiteRateHandler
extends java.lang.Object
implements ProperDependent, InfoProvider
    Handles sequence evolution rate variation across sites using a discretisation approach on top of a gamma distribution.

    The gamma distribution is constrained to have mean 1.0 (meaning it can be parameterised using only the shape parameter k=alpha), and is represented by n discrete site rate categories, where n is a user-defined number. E.g., for n=4, each site rate category represents a quarter of the distribution's probability mass, [0,0.25), [0.25,0.50), [0.50,0.75), [0.75,1.00], and the rate of a category is the mean of the rates over its interval (not mean probability density, mind you).

    Author:
    Bengt Sennblad., Lars Arvestad., Joel Sj√∂strand.

        public void cacheAndUpdate(java.util.Map<Dependent,ChangeInfo> changeInfos,
                  boolean willSample)
        Description copied from interface: ProperDependent
        Caches and updates this object. It may be assumed that this method will only be invoked if a parent has in fact changed.
        Input: All changes made so far, i.e., changes to dependent objects which precede this in the dependency DAG.
        Output: Changes made to this object are added to the input.

        Behaviour must adhere to the following:

        1. This objects queries input for change info of its parents.
        2. This object caches.
        3. This object sets its own change info (null if it has not changed).
        4. Exit.
        Specified by:
        cacheAndUpdate in interface ProperDependent
        Parameters:
        changeInfos - all changes made so far, including those of this objects parents, if any (null is interpreted as no change).
